item.dc:creator: @slump40 slump40
item.description:
@slump40 wrote:

@echo off cd .. "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/players/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/players/update/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/players/items/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/players/combat/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/io/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/io/packets/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/net/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/util/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/world/mapdata/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ./bin/ ./Bulby/world/items/*.java pause

That should work. If not try changing the JDK versions.
